article.headline: Belmont 75, Campbell 50
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Ian Clark scored 14 points to lead Belmont to a 75-50 victory over Campbell on Saturday. Clark hit four 3-pointers as the Bruins (12-10, 7-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) completed a season sweep. They defeated Campbell 66-55 on Jan. 21. Belmont used a 35-8 run to pull away from the Camels (12-8, 7-4) and held their all-time leading scorer, Jonathan Rodriguez, scoreless for the first time in his 111-game career. It also was Campbell's worst loss of the season. The Bruins were 7-for-14 on 3-pointers in the opening half and closed with a 14-2 run to take a 40-23 advantage. Campbell went the final 3:30 without a field goal. Keaton Belcher added 13 points and Kerron Johnson had 12 for Belmont, which shot 57 percent from the field (12-for-21) in the first half and 88.9 percent from the line (24-for-27) for the game. Amir Celestin led Campbell with 12 points.
